Name: A1
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 3/4 shot Gin, 1 Shot Grand Marnier, 1/4 Shot Lemon Juice, 1/8 Shot Grenadine
Instructions: Pour all ingredients into a cocktail shaker, mix and serve over ice into a chilled glass.

Name: ABC
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Shot glass
Ingredients: 1/3 Amaretto, 1/3 Baileys irish cream, 1/3 Cognac
Instructions: Layered in a shot glass.

Name: Ace
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Martini Glass
Ingredients: 2 shots Gin, 1/2 shot Grenadine, 1/2 shot Heavy cream, 1/2 shot Milk, 1/2 Fresh Egg White
Instructions: Shake all the ingredients in a cocktail shaker and ice then strain in a cold glass.

Name: ACID
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Shot glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Bacardi 151 proof rum, 1 oz Wild Turkey
Instructions: Poor in the 151 first followed by the 101 served with a Coke or Dr Pepper chaser.

Name: Adam
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Dark rum, 1 oz Lemon juice, 1 tsp Grenadine
Instructions: In a shaker half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Shake well. Strain into a cocktail glass.

Name: AT&T
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball Glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Absolut Vodka, 1 oz Gin, 4 oz Tonic water
Instructions: Pour Vodka and Gin over ice, add Tonic and Stir

Name: A. J.
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Applejack, 1 oz Grapefruit juice
Instructions: Shake ingredients with ice, strain into a cocktail glass, and serve.

Name: Avalon
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 3 parts Vodka, 1 part Pisang Ambon, 6 parts Apple juice, 1 1/2 part Lemon juice,  Lemonade
Instructions: Fill a tall glass with ice. Layer the Finlandia Vodka, lemon and apple juices, Pisang Ambon, and top up with lemonade. Stir slightly and garnish with a spiralled cucumber skin and a red cherry. The cucumber provides zest and looks attractive. This drink, created by Timo Haimi, took first prize in the 1991 Finlandia Vodka Long Drink Competition.

Name: Apello
Alcoholic: Non alcoholic
Category: Other / Unknown
Glass: Collins Glass
Ingredients: 4 cl Orange juice, 3 cl Grapefruit juice, 1 cl Apple juice, 1 Maraschino cherry
Instructions: Stirr. Grnish with maraschino cherry.

Name: Affair
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Strawberry schnapps, 2 oz Orange juice, 2 oz Cranberry juice,  Club soda
Instructions: Pour schnapps, orange juice, and cranberry juice over ice in a highball glass. Top with club soda and serve.

Name: Abilene
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Dark rum, 2 oz Peach nectar, 3 oz Orange juice
Instructions: Pour all of the ingredients into a highball glass almost filled with ice cubes. Stir well.

Name: Almeria
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Dark rum, 1 oz Kahlua, 1 Egg white
Instructions: In a shaker half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Shake well. Strain into a cocktail glass.

Name: Addison
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Martini Glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 shot Gin, 1 1/2 shot Vermouth
Instructions: Shake together all the ingredients and strain into a cold glass.

Name: Applecar
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Applejack, 1 oz Triple sec, 1 oz Lemon juice
Instructions: Shake all ingredients with ice, strain into a cocktail glass, and serve.

Name: Acapulco
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Old-fashioned glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Light rum, 1 1/2 tsp Triple sec, 1 tblsp Lime juice, 1 tsp Sugar, 1 Egg white, 1 Mint
Instructions: Combine and shake all ingredients (except mint) with ice and strain into an old-fashioned glass over ice cubes. Add the sprig of mint and serve.

Name: Affinity
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Scotch, 1 oz Sweet Vermouth, 1 oz Dry Vermouth, 2 dashes Orange bitters
Instructions: In a mixing glass half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Stir well. Strain into a cocktail glass.

Name: Aviation
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 4.5 cl Gin, 1.5 cl lemon juice, 1.5 cl maraschino liqueur
Instructions: Add all ingredients into cocktail shaker filled with ice. Shake well and strain into cocktail glass. Garnish with a cherry.

Name: After sex
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 2 cl Vodka, 1 cl Creme de Banane,  Orange juice
Instructions: Pour the vodka and creme over some ice cubes in a tall glass and fill up with juice. to make it beuty full make the top of the glass with a grenadine and sugar

Name: Applejack
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Jack Daniels, 1/2 oz Midori melon liqueur, 2 oz Sour mix
Instructions: Add all ingredients into mixing glass, chill and strain into cocktail glass

Name: Afterglow
Alcoholic: Non alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Highball Glass
Ingredients: 1 part Grenadine, 4 parts Orange juice, 4 parts Pineapple juice
Instructions: Mix. Serve over ice.

Name: Afternoon
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Coffee / Tea
Glass: Collins Glass
Ingredients: 1 cl Kahlua, 1 cl Baileys irish cream, 1 1/2 Frangelico, 4 cl hot Coffee,  Cream
Instructions: Build into a suiting glass, with no ice. Cream on top if wanted. Served directly.

Name: Alexander
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1/2 oz Gin, 1/2 oz white Creme de Cacao, 2 oz Light cream,  Nutmeg
Instructions: Shake all ingredients with ice and strain contents into a cocktail glass. Sprinkle nutmeg on top and serve.

Name: Autodafé
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 4 cl Vodka, 1 dash Lime juice,  Soda water
Instructions: Mix and fill up with soda water. Drunk by finns on a sunny day any time of the year and day.

Name: Allegheny
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Dry Vermouth, 1 oz Bourbon, 1 1/2 tsp Blackberry brandy, 1 1/2 tsp Lemon juice, 1 twist of Lemon peel
Instructions: Shake all ingredients (except lemon peel) with ice and strain into a cocktail glass. Top with the twist of lemon peel and serve.

Name: Americano
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Collins glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Campari, 1 oz red Sweet Vermouth, Twist of Lemon peel, Twist of Orange peel
Instructions: Pour the Campari and vermouth over ice into glass, add a splash of soda water and garnish with half orange slice.

Name: B-52
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Shot glass
Ingredients: 1/3 Baileys irish cream, 1/3 Grand Marnier, 1/4 Kahlua
Instructions: Layer ingredients into a shot glass. Serve with a stirrer.

Name: B-53
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Collins Glass
Ingredients: 1/3 shot Kahlua, 1/3 shot Sambuca, 1/3 shot Grand Marnier
Instructions: Layer the Kahlua, Sambucca and Grand Marnier into a shot glas in that order. Better than B-52

Name: Bijou
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 dash Orange Bitters, 1 oz Green Chartreuse, 1 oz Gin, 1 oz Sweet Vermouth
Instructions: Stir in mixing glass with ice and strain

Name: Boxcar
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Whiskey sour glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Gin, 1 oz Triple sec, 1 tsp Lemon juice, 1/2 tsp Grenadine, 1 Egg white
Instructions: In a shaker half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Shake well. Strain into a sour glass.

Name: Big Red
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Shot glass
Ingredients: 1/2 oz Irish cream, 1/2 oz Goldschlager
Instructions: Pour ingredients into 1 ounce shot glass

Name: Bellini
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Champagne Flute
Ingredients: 6 oz Champagne, 1 oz Peach schnapps
Instructions: Pour peach purée into chilled flute, add sparkling wine. Stir gently.

Name: Bramble
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Old-Fashioned glass
Ingredients: 4 cl Gin, 1.5 cl lemon juice, 1 cl Sugar syrup, 1.5 cl Creme de Mure
Instructions: Fill glass with crushed ice. Build gin, lemon juice and simple syrup over. Stir, and then pour blackberry liqueur over in a circular fashion to create marbling effect. Garnish with two blackberries and lemon slice.

Name: Balmoral
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Scotch, 1/2 oz Sweet Vermouth, 1/2 oz Dry Vermouth, 2 dashes Bitters
Instructions: In a mixing glass half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Stir well. Strain into a cocktail glass.

Name: Bluebird
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Gin, 1/2 oz Triple sec, 1/2 oz Blue Curacao, 2 dashes Bitters, 1 Maraschino cherry, 1 twist of Lemon peel
Instructions: In a mixing glass half-filled with crushed ice, combine the gin, triple sec, Curacao, and bitters. Stir well. Strain into a cocktail glass and garnish with the lemon twist and the cherry.

Name: Brooklyn
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Rye Whiskey, 1 oz Dry Vermouth, 1/4 oz Maraschino Liqueur, 3 dashes Angostura Bitters, 1 Maraschino Cherry
Instructions: Combine ingredients with ice and stir until well-chilled. Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.

Name: Bora Bora
Alcoholic: Non alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 10 cl Pineapple juice, 6 cl Passion fruit juice, 1 cl Lemon juice, 1 cl Grenadine
Instructions: Prepare in a blender or shaker, serve in a highball glass on the rocks. Garnish with 1 slice of pineapple and one cherry.

Name: Boomerang
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Gin, 1/2 oz Dry Vermouth, 2 dashes Bitters, 1/2 tsp Maraschino liqueur, 1 Maraschino cherry
Instructions: In a mixing glass half-filled with ice cubes, combine the gin, vermouth, bitters, and maraschino liqueur. Stir well. Strain into a cocktail glass and garnish with the cherry.

Name: Barracuda
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Margarita glass
Ingredients: 4.5 cl Rum, 1.5 cl Galliano, 6 cl Pineapple Juice, 1 dash Lime Juice, top up Prosecco
Instructions: Shake pour ingredients with ice. Strain into glass, top with Sparkling wine.

Name: Brigadier
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Coupe Glass
Ingredients: 4 oz Hot Chocolate, 1 oz Green Chartreuse, 1 oz Cherry Heering
Instructions: Mix ingredients in a warmed mug and stir.

Name: Broadside
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 1 shot 151 proof rum, 1/2 shot Scotch, 3 drops Bitters, 1 Fresh Wormwood, cubes Ice
Instructions: Half fill the glass with ice cubes. Crush the wormwood and add to ice. Pour rum, scotch and butters, then serve!

Name: Buccaneer
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Beer
Glass: Beer pilsner
Ingredients: 1 Corona, 1 shot Bacardi Limon
Instructions: Pour the corona into an 18oz beer glass pour the bacardi limon into the beer stir very gently

Name: Brain Fart
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Punch / Party Drink
Glass: Punch bowl
Ingredients: 1 fifth Everclear, 1 fifth Smirnoff red label Vodka, 2 L Mountain Dew, 2 L Surge, 1 small bottle Lemon juice, 1 pint Rum
Instructions: Mix all ingredients together. Slowly and gently. Works best if ice is added to punch bowl and soda's are very cold.

Name: Blackthorn
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Sweet Vermouth, 1 1/2 oz Sloe gin, 1 twist of Lemon peel
Instructions: Stir sloe gin and vermouth with ice and strain into a cocktail glass. Add the twist of lemon peel and serve.

Name: Bob Marley
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Shot glass
Ingredients: 1/2 oz Midori melon liqueur, 1/2 oz Jägermeister, 1/2 oz Goldschlager
Instructions: Layer in a 2 oz shot glass or pony glass

Name: Bible Belt
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Other / Unknown
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Southern Comfort, 1/2 oz Triple sec, 2 wedges Lime, 2 oz Sour mix
Instructions: Mix all ingredients, and pour over ice.

Name: Bubble Gum
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Shot glass
Ingredients: 1/4 Vodka, 1/4 Banana liqueur, 1/4 Orange juice, 1/4 Peach schnapps
Instructions: Layer in order into a shot glass.

Name: Bumble Bee
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Shot glass
Ingredients: 1/3 oz Baileys irish cream, 1/3 oz Kahlua, 1/3 oz Sambuca
Instructions: This is a layered shot. First pour the Bailey's into the shot glass. Then take an upside down spoon and touch it to the inside wall of the glass. Carefully add the Kahlua. Repeat this process for the Sambuca. If done properly, the alcohol will stay separated and resemble a bumble bee. Enjoy!!!

Name: Baby Eskimo
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shake
Glass: Collins Glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Kahlua, 8 oz Milk, 2 scoops Vanilla ice-cream
Instructions: Leave ice-cream out for about 10 minutes. Add ingredients in order, stir with chopstick (butter knife or spoon works too). Consume immediately and often. Nice and light, great for following a heavy drink.

Name: Boston Sour
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Whiskey sour glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Blended whiskey, Juice of 1/2 Lemon, 1 tsp Powdered sugar, 1 Egg white, 1 slice Lemon, 1 Cherry
Instructions: Shake juice of lemon, powdered sugar, blended whiskey, and egg white with cracked ice and strain into a whiskey sour glass. Add the slice of lemon, top with the cherry, and serve.

Name: Bahama Mama
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 3 parts Rum, 1 part Dark Rum, 1 part Banana liqueur, 1 part Grenadine, 2 parts Pineapple Juice, 2 parts Orange Juice, 1 part Sweet and Sour
Instructions: Add 2 parts club soda or more or less to taste.

Mix it all together and pour over a bunch of ice. Drink with a straw.

Name: Casino
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Gin, 1/4 tsp Maraschino liqueur, 1/4 tsp Lemon juice, 2 dashes Orange bitters, 1 Cherry
Instructions: Pour all ingredients into shaker with ice cubes. Shake well. Strain into chilled cocktail glass. Garnish with a lemon twist and a maraschino cherry. Serve without a straw.

Name: Cafe Savoy
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Coffee / Tea
Glass: Coffee mug
Ingredients:  Coffee, 1/2 oz Milk, 1/2 oz Triple sec,  Brandy
Instructions: Fill mug almost to top with coffee.Add milk, triple sec and brandy. Stir.

Name: Caipirinha
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Old-fashioned glass
Ingredients: 2 tsp Sugar, 1 Lime, 2 1/2 oz Cachaca
Instructions: Place lime and sugar into old fashioned glass and muddle (mash the two ingredients together using a muddler or a wooden spoon). Fill the glass with ice and add the Cachaça.

Name: Cream Soda
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Spiced rum,  Ginger ale
Instructions: Pour 1oz of Spiced Rum into a highball glass with ice. Fill with Ginger Ale.

Name: Cuba Libra
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 1-2 shot Dark rum, Squeeze Lime, Fill with Coca-Cola,  Ice
Instructions: Fill tall glass with ice cubes. Add rum. Rub cut edge of lime on rim of glass then squeeze juice into glass. Fill with Coca-Cola. Garnish with lime slice. Enjoy!

Name: Cherry Rum
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 1/4 oz Light rum, 1 1/2 tsp Cherry brandy, 1 tblsp Light cream
Instructions: Shake all ingredients with ice, strain into a cocktail glass, and serve.

Name: Cuba Libre
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Light rum, Juice of 1/2 Lime,  Coca-Cola
Instructions: Build all ingredients in a Collins glass filled with ice. Garnish with lime wedge.

Name: Corn n Oil
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Old-fashioned glass
Ingredients: 1/2 Lime, 1/3 oz Falernum, 2 dashes Angostura Bitters, 1 oz Añejo rum, 1 oz blackstrap rum
Instructions: Cut the half lime in half again. Add the lime, falernum, and bitters to a rocks glass. Muddle. Add the rum. (Aged Barbados rum such as Plantation 5 Year is recommended). Add ice and stir. Float the blackstrap rum on top. Serve with a straw.

Name: Citrus Coke
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Soft Drink
Glass: Highball Glass
Ingredients: 1 part Bacardi Limon, 2 parts Coca-Cola
Instructions: Pour half of coke in a glass. Then add Bacardi and top it off with the remaining coke. Stir and drink up!

Name: Casa Blanca
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Light rum, 1 1/2 tsp Triple sec, 1 1/2 tsp Lime juice, 1 1/2 tsp Maraschino liqueur
Instructions: Shake all ingredients with ice, strain into a cocktail glass, and serve.

Name: Clover Club
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Gin, 2 tsp Grenadine, Juice of 1/2 Lemon, 1 Egg white
Instructions: Dry shake ingredients to emulsify, add ice, shake and served straight up.

Name: Caipirissima
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Collins Glass
Ingredients: 2 Lime, 2 tblsp Sugar, 2-3 oz White rum, crushed Ice
Instructions: Same as Caipirinha but instead of cachaca you add WHITE RUM. It's great!!!!!!!!

Name: City Slicker
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Brandy, 1/2 oz Triple sec, 1 tblsp Lemon juice
Instructions: In a shaker half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Shake well. Strain into a cocktail glass.

Name: Campari Beer
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Beer
Glass: Beer mug
Ingredients: 1 bottle Lager, 1 1/2 cl Campari
Instructions: Use a 15 oz glass. Add Campari first. Fill with beer.

Name: Chicago Fizz
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Light rum, 1 oz Port, Juice of 1/2 Lemon, 1 tsp Powdered sugar, 1 Egg white,  Carbonated water
Instructions: Shake all ingredients (except carbonated water) with ice and strain into a highball glass over two ice cubes. Fill with carbonated water, stir, and serve.

Name: Cosmopolitan
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 1/4 oz Vodka, 1/4 oz Lime juice, 1/4 oz Cointreau, 1/4 cup Cranberry juice
Instructions: Add all ingredients into cocktail shaker filled with ice. Shake well and double strain into large cocktail glass. Garnish with lime wheel.

Name: Coffee-Vodka
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Homemade Liqueur
Glass: Collins Glass
Ingredients: 2 cups Water, 2 cups white Sugar, 1/2 cup instant Coffee, 1/2 Vanilla, 1 1/2 cup Vodka,  Caramel coloring
Instructions: Boil water and sugar until dissolved. Turn off heat. Slowly add dry instant coffee and continue stirring. Add a chopped vanilla bean to the vodka, then combine the cooled sugar syrup and coffee solution with the vodka. Cover tightly and shake vigorously each day for 3 weeks. Strain and filter. Its also best to let the sugar mixture cool completely so the vodka won't evaporate when its added. If you like a smoother feel to the liqueur you can add about 1 teaspoon of glycerine to the finished product.

Name: Casino Royale
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Whiskey sour glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Gin, 1/2 oz Lemon juice, 1 tsp Maraschino liqueur, 1 dash Orange bitters, 1 Egg yolk
Instructions: In a shaker half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Shake well. Strain into a sour glass.

Name: Corpse Reviver
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 3/4 oz Gin, 3/4 oz Triple Sec, 3/4 oz Lillet Blanc, 3/4 oz Lemon Juice, 1 dash Absinthe
Instructions: Shake, strain, straight up, cocktail glass rinsed with absinthe

Name: Chocolate Milk
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Shot Glass
Ingredients: 1/2 shot Chocolate liqueur, 1/2 shot Milk, 1 dash Amaretto
Instructions: Put the milk in the bottom, pour the Liquer on top and add the dash of amaretto. Do not mix. SLAM IT!

Name: Clove Cocktail
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 oz Sweet Vermouth, 1/2 oz Sloe gin, 1/2 oz Muscatel Wine
Instructions: Stir all ingredients with ice, strain into a cocktail glass, and serve.

Name: Coffee Liqueur
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Homemade Liqueur
Glass: Collins Glass
Ingredients: 10 tblsp instant Coffee, 4 tblsp Vanilla extract, 2 1/2 cups Sugar, 1 qt Vodka, 2 1/2 cups Water
Instructions: Combine coffee, sugar and water. Simmer 1 hour and let cool. Add vanilla and vodka. Age in sealed jar 2 to 3 weeks.

Name: Coke and Drops
Alcoholic: Non alcoholic
Category: Soft Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 dl Coca-Cola, 7 drops Lemon juice
Instructions: Take a glass, pour the Coke in the glass, then you take 7 drops of lemon juice. Granish with a lemon slice on the rim of the glass.

Name: Chocolate Drink
Alcoholic: Non alcoholic
Category: Cocoa
Glass: Coffee mug
Ingredients: 125 gr Chocolate, 3/4 L Milk,  Water
Instructions: Melt the bar in a small amount of boiling water. Add milk. Cook over low heat, whipping gently (with a whisk, i would assume) until heated well. Don't let it boil! Serve in coffee mug.

Name: Cranberry Punch
Alcoholic: Non alcoholic
Category: Punch / Party Drink
Glass: Punch Bowl
Ingredients: 4 cups Cranberry juice, 1 1/2 cup Sugar, 4 cups Pineapple juice, 1 tblsp Almond flavoring, 2 qt Ginger ale
Instructions: Combine first four ingredients. Stir until sugar is dissolved, chill. Then add ginger ale just before serving. Add ice ring to keep punch cold.

Name: Derby
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 6 cl gin, 2 dashes Peach Bitters, 2 Fresh leaves Mint
Instructions: Pour all ingredients into a mixing glass with ice. Stir. Strain into a cocktail glass. Garnish with a sprig of fresh mint in the drink.

Name: Diesel
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Beer
Glass: Pint glass
Ingredients: 1/2 pint Lager, 1/2 pint Cider, 1 dash Blackcurrant cordial
Instructions: Pour the lager first then add the blackcurrant cordial. Top up with the cider. The colour sholud be very dark approaching the colour of Guiness.

Name: Daiquiri
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Light rum, Juice of 1/2 Lime, 1 tsp Powdered sugar
Instructions: Pour all ingredients into shaker with ice cubes. Shake well. Strain in chilled cocktail glass.

Name: Danbooka
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Coffee / Tea
Glass: Coffee Mug
Ingredients: 3 parts Coffee, 1 part Everclear
Instructions: pour it in and mix it.

Name: Downshift
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Punch / Party Drink
Glass: Hurricane glass
Ingredients: 2 part Fruit punch, 1 part Sprite, 2 shots Tequila, Float Bacardi 151 proof rum
Instructions: Start with the Sprite. Next comes the tequila. After that, add the Minute Maid Fruit Punch, then float the 151. Rocks optional.

Name: Dragonfly
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 1 1/2 oz Gin, 4 oz Ginger ale, 1 Lime
Instructions: In a highball glass almost filled with ice cubes, combine the gin and ginger ale. Stir well. Garnish with the lime wedge.

Name: Dry Martini
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 2/3 oz Gin, 1/3 oz Dry Vermouth, 1 Olive
Instructions: Straight: Pour all ingredients into mixing glass with ice cubes. Stir well. Strain in chilled martini cocktail glass. Squeeze oil from lemon peel onto the drink, or garnish with olive.

Name: Dry Rob Roy
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 2 1/2 oz Scotch, 1 1/2 tsp Dry Vermouth, 1 twist of Lemon peel
Instructions: In a mixing glass half-filled with ice cubes, combine the Scotch and vermouth. Stir well. Strain into a cocktail glass. Garnish with the lemon twist.

Name: Dirty Nipple
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Shot
Glass: Shot glass
Ingredients:  Kahlua,  Sambuca,  Baileys irish cream
Instructions: This is a layered shot - the Bailey's must be on top

Name: Dirty Martini
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 70ml/2fl oz Vodka, 1 tbsp Dry Vermouth, 2 tbsp Olive Brine, 1 wedge Lemon, 1 Olive
Instructions: Pour the vodka, dry vermouth and olive brine into a cocktail shaker with a handful of ice and shake well.
Rub the rim of a martini glass with the wedge of lemon.
Strain the contents of the cocktail shaker into the glass and add the olive.
A dirty Martini contains a splash of olive brine or olive juice and is typically garnished with an olive.

Name: Darkwood Sling
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Soft Drink
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 1 part Cherry Heering, 1 part Soda water, 1 part Orange juice, cubes Ice
Instructions: There are many good cherry liqueurs you can use, but I prefere Heering. Add one share of the liqueur. Then you add one share of Soda. For a sour sling use Tonic (most people prefer the drink without Tonic). Afterwards you fill the glass with Orange Juice and ice cubes.

Name: Dark and Stormy
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Ordinary Drink
Glass: Highball glass
Ingredients: 5 cl Dark Rum, 10 cl Ginger Beer
Instructions: In a highball glass filled with ice add 6cl dark rum and top with ginger beer. Garnish with lime wedge.

Name: Dark Caipirinha

Name: Empellón Cocina's Fat-Washed Mezcal
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Beer Glass
Ingredients: 2 oz Mezcal, 3/4 oz Chocolate liqueur, 1/2 oz Coffee liqueur
Instructions: To ensure that your pork fat is just as delicious as theirs, here’s their adobo marinade and what to do with it (you’ll also need a rack of ribs):

4 ancho chiles, 8 guajillo chiles and 4 chipotle chiles, plus 4 cloves roasted garlic, half a cup of cider vinegar, a quarter teaspoon of Mexican oregano, 1 teaspoon of ground black pepper, a whole clove, a quarter teaspoon of ground cinnamon and a half teaspoon of ground cumin.

Toast the dried chiles and soak in water for at least an hour until they are rehydrated. Drain and discard the soaking liquid. Combine the soaked chiles with the remaining ingredients and purée until smooth.

Cold smoke a rack of baby back pork ribs by taking a large hotel pan with woodchips on one side and charcoal on the other. Place another, smaller, pan with pork ribs, above the charcoal/woodchip pan. Ignite the charcoal, being careful to not ignite the woodchips. Cover both pans with foil and allow to smoke for 10-15 minutes, until desired level of smoke is achieved, then coat with adobo marinade and wrap in tin foil prior to placing ribs in a 300 degree oven for 7 hours. When the ribs have cooled, strain off the fat and use for the infusion.

If you’re having a hard time coming up to the same kind of volume of fat, make up the balance with pork lard from a butcher. To get the same depth of flavor without the ribs, heat up the fat in a pot with a few spoons of the marinade.

Once you’ve got your tub of seasoned pork fat in cooled liquid form, pour equal amounts of Ilegal Joven mezcal and fat into a sealable container. Seal the container and give it a really good shake, then put it in the freezer overnight. When the whole thing is separated and congealed, pour it through a fine mesh chinoise. If you don’t have a chinoise, try a fine mesh strainer, or if you don’t have one of those, try spooning off most of the fat. There will be some beads of orange fat left in the strained mezcal: run that through a few layers of cheesecloth (or coffee filters in a pinch) to get rid of the last of it.

The mezcal is now ready for drinking, straight-up or in a cocktail. 

Habanero tincture

Slice habaneros and add 2 ounces Ilegal Joven mezcal.
Allow to sit overnight or until desired level of heat is achieved.
Cocktail

Combine mezcal and chocolate liqueur in a mixing glass with ice and stir for 45 seconds.
Strain into chilled coupe.
Carefully "sink" the coffee liqueur down the inside of the coupe over a spoon.
Garnish with 5 drops habanero tincture.

Name: Frosé
Alcoholic: Alcoholic
Category: Cocktail
Glass: Cocktail glass
Ingredients: 750 ml Rose, 1/2 cup Sugar, 8 oz Strawberries, 2-3 oz Lemon Juice
Instructions: Step 1
Pour rosé into a 13x9" pan and freeze until almost solid (it won't completely solidify due to the alcohol), at least 6 hours.

Step 2
Meanwhile, bring sugar and ½ cup water to a boil in a medium saucepan; cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves, about 3 minutes. Add strawberries, remove from heat, and let sit 30 minutes to infuse syrup with strawberry flavor. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve into a small bowl (do not press on solids); cover and chill until cold, about 30 minutes.

Step 3
Scrape rosé into a blender. Add lemon juice, 3½ ounces strawberry syrup, and 1 cup crushed ice and purée until smooth. Transfer blender jar to freezer and freeze until frosé is thickened (aim for milkshake consistency), 25–35 minutes.

Step 4
Blend again until frosé is slushy. Divide among glasses.

Step 5
Do Ahead: Rosé can be frozen 1 week ahead.

Instructions: Vampiros may be made in a tall glass or an old fashioned glass. Bartenders may first "rim" the glass with Kosher Salt, which is done by placing a layer of Kosher Salt on a chopping board, moistening the glass' rim with lime juice or water, and then placing the upside down glass rim onto the Kosher Salt, so that the salt sticks to the moistened rim. The second step is to fill half the glass with ice and add one or two shooter glasses full of high quality Tequila. The next stage is to add the flavouring elements. This is done by squeezing a fresh lime into the glass, adding a few grains of salt, adding citrus-flavoured soda pop, until the glass is 4/5 full, and then adding spicy Viuda de Sanchez (or orange juice, lime juice and pico de gallo). The final step is to stir the ingredients so that the flavours are properly blended.
